@startuml
' ==========================================================
' Diagramme de classes participantes — Cas d’utilisation : Créer un projet
' Objectif : classes impliquées dans la création + soumission IA
' Alignement : `backend/routes/api/projectRoutes.js`, `backend/services/projectService.js`, queues IA
' ==========================================================

title Diagramme de classes participantes — UC "Créer un projet"
left to right direction
skinparam dpi 160
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam wrapWidth 240

class ProjectRoutes <<controller>> {
  +POST /api/projects()
  +POST /api/projects/:id/submit-for-ai()
  +PUT /api/projects/:id()
  +PUT /api/projects/:id/resubmit()
}

class ProjectService <<service>> {
  +createDraftProject(creatorId, données)
  +submitProjectForAi(creatorId, projectId)
  +updateProject(creatorId, projectId, changes)
  +resubmitRejectedProject(creatorId, projectId, changes)
}

class Project <<model>> {
  +creatorId
  +title
  +description
  +category
  +fundingGoal
  +currentFunding
  +status
  +startAt
  +deadline
  +aiAnalysis
}

class RiskAnalysisQueue <<integration>> {
  +enqueueRiskAnalysisJob(project)
}

class WorkflowInternalService <<service>> {
  +buildRiskPayload(project)
  +updateAiAnalysisFromWorkflow(...)
}

ProjectRoutes ..> ProjectService
ProjectService ..> Project
ProjectService ..> RiskAnalysisQueue
RiskAnalysisQueue ..> WorkflowInternalService : buildRiskPayload(project)

note bottom of Project
  Le statut évolue selon le cycle de vie\n
  (ex. DRAFT -> AWAITING_AI -> ACTIVE/REJECTED/...)
end note

@enduml

